{"word":"H7857 - שָׁטַף - shâṭaph - shaw-taf' - Drown","slug":"H7857","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שָׁטַף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>shâṭaph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>shaw-taf'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Drown"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D8;&#x05E3; - sha&#x0302;t&#x0323;aph</b> - <i>shaw-taf'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>gush</i>; by implication to <i>inundate</i>, <i>cleanse</i>; by analogy to <i>gallop</i>, <i>conquer: - </i>drown, (over-) flow (-whelm), rinse, run, rush, (throughly) wash (away)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7858\">H7858</a>, <a href=\"#/H8241\">H8241</a>"}]}